'''''Motor Mania''''' is a top-down, vertically scrolling [[racing game]] written by John Fitzpatrick for the [[Commodore 64]] and published by UMI in 1982,<ref name="giantlist"/> the year the system was released.

==Gameplay==
{{expand section|date=August 2017}}
The player drives an old-style racing car through different types of tracks avoiding enemy drivers, obstacles on the road such as nails, oil,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/your64-magazine-01/page/n44/mode/2up |title=Action Replay |magazine=Your 64 |issue=1 | date=April 1984 |page=43}}</ref> broken glass, boulders and a fire engine at a crossroad. The game has 9 levels of difficulty.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/personalcomputergames-magazine-01/page/n97/mode/2up|title = Personal Computer Games Magazine Issue 01}}</ref>

